methodsArray.push( [ 'CostanzoRecipes_Entrees_Pizza', '</div>  <!-- <h3> --><h3 id="header-section-section-3" onclick="toggleSection(\'section-3\')">Crust<span id="heading-ellipses-section-3"></h3><div id=\'heading-content-section-3\'><p><ol><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Soften yeast in water. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Add salt then start adding flour until a wet dough forms. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Knead briefly, just to form a consistent dough. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Place ball of dough in <amount original_amount="a large" fraction="1.000000000000" units="large">a large</amount> plastic Ziploc bag (or large bowl) that has been coated with olive oil.</li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Place in refrigerator for 4-5 hours. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-4\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-4" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-4", 14400)</script><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-4", 18000)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> About the time you turn the oven on to pre-heat, pull dough out of refrigerator. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Punch down and then let rest for 10 minutes. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-5\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-5" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-5", 600)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Divide ball in half and coat well with flour. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Start patting each ball of dough out into a circle, the thinner the better, letting rest if it won\'t spread out. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Place an oven rack at the very lowest position; remove other racks and set aside. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Place baking tiles or pizza stone on the rack and preheat the oven to 500 F for an hour or so. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-6\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-6" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-6", 3600)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Make sure stone is in the oven from the beginning otherwise the high heat might crack it. </li></ol></div>  <!-- <h3> --><h3 id="header-section-section-7" onclick="toggleSection(\'section-7\')">New York Style Tomato Sauce<span id="heading-ellipses-section-7"></h3><div id=\'heading-content-section-7\'><p><ol><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Crush the tomatoes with your hands or a fork and place in a heavy saucepan over medium heat. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Stir in the tomato paste, garlic, oregano and salt and pepper to taste. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Bring the mixture just to a boil, then reduce the heat to low and simmer the sauce, stirring occasionally, until thick and flavorful, 30 minutes to 1 hour. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-8\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-8" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-8", 1800)</script><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-8", 0)</script><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-8", 3600)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Remove from the heat. (This may be stored in the refrigerator for up to 1 week or frozen up to 4 months) </li></ol></div>  <!-- <h3> --><h3 id="header-section-section-9" onclick="toggleSection(\'section-9\')">To bake<span id="heading-ellipses-section-9"></h3><div id=\'heading-content-section-9\'><p><ol><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Turn the smoke alarm off. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Cover pizza peel with coarse corn meal. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Place one flattened piece of the dough onto the peel, spread with olive oil, cover with a thick layer of tomato sauce then add toppings. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Sprinkle on a thick layer of parmesan cheese then drizzle with olive oil. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Slide pizza onto the hot stone and bake 10 to 15 minutes until the top of the pie is beginning to brown. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-10\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-10" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-10", 600)</script><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-10", 900)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Remove pizza from oven and place on a cutting board. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Let sit for a few minutes then slice and eat while hot. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-11\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-11" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-11", 120)</script><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-11", 300)</script></div></li></ol>' ] );
