methodsArray.push( [ 'CostanzoRecipes_Entrees_GarlicWhitePizzaSauce', '<p><ol><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> In a skillet on medium-high heat, heat oil. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Add the garlic and heat for about 3 minutes, until fragrant. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-1\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-1" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-1", 180)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Add the flour (start with <amount original_amount="2 tablespoons" fraction="2.000000000000" units="tablespoons">2 tablespoons</amount>), oregano, pepper, and salt; whisk well.</li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Add the half & half all at once, whisking constantly; cook and stir until bubbly and until thickened (usually about 3 minutes). <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-2\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-2" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-2", 180)</script></div></li></ol><p><div class="tip"> If you want the sauce a bit thicker, mix your remaining <amount original_amount="1 tablespoon" fraction="1.000000000000" units="tablespoon">1 tablespoon</amount> of flour with a bit of milk until you have a mashed potato consistency. Pour that mixture into the bubbling sauce and whisk constantly. Cook about 1 minute more. It should thicken the sauce. Repeat until you have it the thickness you want.<img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-3\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-3" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-3", 60)</script></div></div>' ] );
