methodsArray.push( [ 'CostanzoRecipes_Entrees_FreshEggPasta', '<p><ol><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Place the flour in the work bowl of a food processor and pulse several times. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Add the eggs and process until the dough forms a rough ball, about 30 seconds. (If the dough refuses to come together, add water, <amount original_amount="½ teaspoon" fraction="0.500000000000" units="teaspoon">½ teaspoon</amount> at a time, and continue processing until a ball forms. If the dough sticks to the sides of the work bowl, add flour, <amount original_amount="1 tablespoon" fraction="1.000000000000" units="tablespoon">1 tablespoon</amount> at a time, and continue processing until a ball forms.)<img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-1\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-1" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-1", 30)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Turn the dough out onto a dry work surface. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Knead by hand until the dough is smooth, 1 to 2 minutes. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-2\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-2" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-2", 60)</script><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-2", 120)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Cover with plastic wrap and set aside for 15 to 30 minutes. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-3\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-3" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-3", 900)</script><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-3", 1800)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Cut about one quarter of the dough from the ball and flatten the piece into a disk (Rewrap the remaining dough.) </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Run the dough through the widest setting on a manual pasta machine. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Bring the ends of the dough toward the middle of the sheet of pasta and press them together. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Run the dough, open side first, through the widest setting again. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Fold , seal and roll again. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Without folding, run the pasta through the widest setting two more times, or until the dough is smooth. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> If at any point the dough seems sticky, lightly dust it with flour. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Continue to run the dough through the pasta machine, narrowing the setting each time. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> When you reach the last setting, the outline of your hand should be visible through the pasta. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Lay the sheet of pasta on a dry kitchen towel and cover with a second towel. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-4\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-4" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-4", 1)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Repeat with the reset of the dough. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> If using the pasta for lasagna, ravioli or tortellini, proceed with the recipe. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> If making fettuccine, take the first sheet of pasta (it will have had a little time to dry out but should not be tough or brittle) and run it through the getting cutters on the pasta machine. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Carefully spread out the fettuccine on kitchen towels. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Repeat with the remaining sheets, making sure they have dried for 15 to 20 minutes before butting. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-5\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-5" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-5", 900)</script><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-5", 1200)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Use the pasta within a few hours or place it in zipper-lock plastic bags and freeze for up to several months. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-6\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-6" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-6", 7200)</script><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-6", 18000)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> When you are ready to cook the pasta, bring <amount original_amount="4 quarts" fraction="4.000000000000" units="quarts">4 quarts</amount> of water to a boil in a large pot.</li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Add salt to taste and the fettuccine. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Fresh pasta will be ready in about 3 minutes. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-7\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-7" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-7", 180)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Frozen pasta should not be defrosted before cooking; it will require 4 to 5 minutes cooking time. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-8\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-8" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-8", 240)</script><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-8", 300)</script></div></li></ol>' ] );
