methodsArray.push( [ 'CostanzoRecipes_Bread_SandwichBread', '<p><ol><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Mix the yeast and sugar with <amount original_amount="¼ cup" fraction="0.250000000000" units="cup">¼ cup</amount> of water and set aside for five minutes until it froths, indicating yeast is active.<img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-1\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-1" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-1", 300)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> To the yeast and water mixture, mix in the remaining cup of water, milk, salt and oil. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Add the flour. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Mix in a stand mixer on low speed or by hand until a dough forms. <div class="note">    If it\'s sticky, continue adding more bread flour, a little at a time, until you have a soft and supple but not sticky or tacky dough. </div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Continue kneading for another 10 minutes. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-2\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-2" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-2", 600)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Form a smooth ball with the dough and place in an oiled bowl, turning over once to cover the top with oil. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Cover and let it rise in a warm place for 1 to 1½ hours, until doubled in volume. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-3\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-3" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-3", 3600)</script><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-3", 5400)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Punch down the dough, form into a ball, and return it to the bowl to rise for another hour. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-4\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-4" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-4", 3600)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Grease two standard (6-cup) loaf pans. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Now punch the dough down again and divide it into two. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Using a rolling pin, roll out each loaf into a rectangle, about 6 x 8 inches. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Roll it up into a cylinder and tuck the seams underneath. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Place each loaf into a loaf pan.</li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Cover the dough loosely with oiled cling wrap or with a shower cap, and set it aside to rise for about 1 hour until the dough rises above the pan, forming a nice dome. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-5\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-5" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-5", 3600)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Preheat the oven to 400°. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Bake the loaves for 35-45 minutes. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-6\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-6" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-6", 2100)</script><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-6", 2700)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Cool on a rack for about 10 minutes, then remove the loaves from the pan and continue cooling before you slice. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-7\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-7" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-7", 600)</script></div></li></ol>' ] );
