creditsArray.push( [ 'CostanzoRecipes_Bread_PandeCristal', '<p><ul><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> From <a href="https://www.kingarthurbaking.com/recipes/pan-de-cristal-recipe" target="_blank">https://www.kingarthurbaking.com/recipes/pan-de-cristal-recipe</a>  </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> date created: [2022-02-01 Tue]   </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)">[2022-02-01 Tue]  This recipe has crazy high hydration. But it gives good directions, including videos of how to do the folds, which really do strengthen the dough. The one issue is that the bake time is way too long: 15 minutes on a hot stone and then perhaps 5 more on a rack is all that is required. More than that and you get some pretty dark crust. The bread was light and crispy, with about as much flavor as you can expect from a same-day bread. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-9\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-9" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-9", 900)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)">[2022-03-26 Sat]  They really only need that first 15 minutes... <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-10\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-10" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-10", 900)</script></div></li></ul>' ] );
ingredientsArray.push( [ 'CostanzoRecipes_Bread_PaindeCampagne', '<h3 id="header-section-section-1" onclick="toggleSection(\'section-1\')">Levain<span id="heading-ellipses-section-1"></h3><div id=\'heading-content-section-1\'><p><ul><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> <amount original_amount="50 g" fraction="50.000000000000" units="g">50 g</amount> mature whole wheat starter</li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> <amount original_amount="100 g" fraction="100.000000000000" units="g">100 g</amount> water</li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> <amount original_amount="100 g" fraction="100.000000000000" units="g">100 g</amount> whole wheat flour</li></ul></div>  <!-- <h3> --><h3 id="header-section-section-2" onclick="toggleSection(\'section-2\')">Main Dough<span id="heading-ellipses-section-2"></h3><div id=\'heading-content-section-2\'><p><ul><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> <amount original_amount="200 g" fraction="200.000000000000" units="g">200 g</amount> of the levain</li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> <amount original_amount="350 g" fraction="350.000000000000" units="g">350 g</amount> water</li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> <amount original_amount="50 g" fraction="50.000000000000" units="g">50 g</amount> rye</li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> <amount original_amount="½ tsp" fraction="0.500000000000" units="tsp">½ tsp</amount> diastatic malt</li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> <amount original_amount="450 g" fraction="450.000000000000" units="g">450 g</amount> bread flour</li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> <amount original_amount="10 g" fraction="10.000000000000" units="g">10 g</amount> salt (about <amount original_amount="0.56 Tablespoons" fraction="0.560000000000" units="Tablespoons">0.56 Tablespoons</amount>)</li></ul>' ] );
methodsArray.push( [ 'CostanzoRecipes_Bread_PaindeCampagne', '<p><ol><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Mix levain ingredients. Allow to peak, between four and five hours in a 28 degrees C kitchen. It ought to have a nice fruity aroma that wasn\'t at all sour. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-3\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-3" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-3", 18000)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Disperse the levain in the water with a wire whisk until it has a good foam on top. Next, whisk in rye and malt powder. Then add bread flour with spatula and mix until all the flour has been moistened. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Autolyse for 50 minutes. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-4\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-4" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-4", 3000)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Add salt. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Knead to medium gluten development. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Bulk ferment for 1 hour with a turn at 30 minutes. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-5\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-5" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-5", 3600)</script><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-5", 1800)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Pre-shape dough and allow to rest for 10 minutes. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-6\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-6" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-6", 600)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Shape final dough and put into well-floured banneton. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Let rise for about half an hour, covered. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-7\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-7" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-7", 1800)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Retard dough for 12 hours in the refrigerator. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-8\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-8" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-8", 43200)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Insert baking stone and preheat oven to 230 degrees C (= 446 degrees F) for 30 minutes. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-9\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-9" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-9", 1800)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Bake with steam for 15 minutes. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-10\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-10" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-10", 900)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Reduce heat to <amount original_amount="200 C" fraction="200.000000000000" units="C">200 C</amount> (= 392 degrees F) and bake for a further 30 - 35 minutes until golden brown.<img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-11\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-11" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-11", 1800)</script><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-11", 2100)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Cool completely on a wire rack. </li></ol>' ] );
creditsArray.push( [ 'CostanzoRecipes_Bread_PaindeCampagne', '<p><a href="http://www.thefreshloaf.com/node/38229/pain-de-campagne" target="_blank">http://www.thefreshloaf.com/node/38229/pain-de-campagne</a>  </div>  <!-- <h3> --><h3 id="header-section-section-12" onclick="toggleSection(\'section-12\')">[2019-07-06 Sat] icymi<span id="heading-ellipses-section-12"></h3><div id=\'heading-content-section-12\'><p><ul><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> My starter was comprised of white flour and I used KA AP flour instead of bread flour and all of the levain. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> I skipped the 12 hour dough retard. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-13\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-13" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-13", 43200)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> I made a double batch. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"><b>Issue</b> : the <amount original_amount="two loaves" fraction="2.000000000000" units="loaves">two loaves</amount> ran together on the peel and stone. I had to saw them apart while they were in the oven.</li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Good oven spring. Moist, with a nice crumb and not too sour (although T disagreed on the latter point). </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Made French toast the next morning, but, frankly, the bread was better as plain ol\' toast. </li></ul>' ] );
ingredientsArray.push( [ 'CostanzoRecipes_Bread_PainauLevain', '<p> Makes <amount original_amount="2 loaves" fraction="2.000000000000" units="loaves">2 loaves</amount><p><ul><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> <amount original_amount="454 grams" fraction="454.000000000000" units="grams">454 grams</amount> ripe starter (<amount original_amount="2½ cups" fraction="2.500000000000" units="cups">2½ cups</amount>; <amount original_amount="1 pound" fraction="1.000000000000" units="pound">1 pound</amount>)</li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> <amount original_amount="600 grams" fraction="600.000000000000" units="grams">600 grams</amount> unbleached, all-purpose flour (<amount original_amount="5 cups" fraction="5.000000000000" units="cups">5 cups</amount>; <amount original_amount="1 pound" fraction="1.000000000000" units="pound">1 pound</amount>, <amount original_amount="5 oz" fraction="5.000000000000" units="oz">5 oz</amount>.)</li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> <amount original_amount="85 grams" fraction="85.000000000000" units="grams">85 grams</amount> whole wheat flour (<amount original_amount="⅔ cups" fraction="0.666666666666" units="cups">⅔ cups</amount>; <amount original_amount="3 oz" fraction="3.000000000000" units="oz">3 oz</amount>.)</li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> <amount original_amount="397 grams" fraction="397.000000000000" units="grams">397 grams</amount> water (<amount original_amount="1¾ cups" fraction="1.750000000000" units="cups">1¾ cups</amount>; <amount original_amount="14 oz" fraction="14.000000000000" units="oz">14 oz</amount>.)</li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> <amount original_amount="12.5 grams" fraction="12.500000000000" units="grams">12.5 grams</amount> (<amount original_amount="2½ teaspoons" fraction="2.500000000000" units="teaspoons">2½ teaspoons</amount>) salt</li></ul>' ] );
methodsArray.push( [ 'CostanzoRecipes_Bread_PainauLevain', '<p><ol><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Combine the flours, water and starter and mix using bread attachment of a mixer. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Cover the bowl loosely with plastic and let the dough rest for 20 to 30 minutes. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-1\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-1" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-1", 1200)</script><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-1", 1800)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Add the salt and knead the dough until it becomes smooth, supple and slightly tacky. (Avoid adding flour!) </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Cover and let rise for 1 hour. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-2\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-2" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-2", 3600)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Fold dough. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Cover and let rise for 1 hour. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-3\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-3" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-3", 3600)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Divide the dough into <amount original_amount="two pieces" fraction="2.000000000000" units="pieces">two pieces</amount> and preshape each piece into a loose ball. Place the dough smooth side up on a lightly floured surface. Cover and let rest for about 20 minutes.<img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-4\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-4" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-4", 1200)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Shape the loaves into loaves and place in loaf pan. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Cover and let rise for 2 hours. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-5\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-5" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-5", 7200)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> An hour before baking, preheat oven to 450 degrees. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-6\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-6" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-6", 3600)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Spritz loaves with water and place in oven. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Bake for 40 minutes, until the crust is richly colored and the internal temperature of the loaf is about 200 degrees. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-7\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-7" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-7", 2400)</script></div></li></ol>' ] );
