methodsArray.push( [ 'CostanzoRecipes_Bread_CrustyHomemadeBread', '<p><ol><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water. Using a rubber spatula, stir in <amount original_amount="3.5 cups" fraction="3.500000000000" units="cups">3.5 cups</amount> flour and salt to form a soft, sticky dough. Do not knead. Cover and let rise at room temperature 1 hour.<img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-1\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-1" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-1", 3600)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Stir down dough (dough will be sticky). Turn onto a floured surface; with floured hands pat into a 9-in. square. Fold square into thirds, forming a 9x3-in. rectangle. Fold rectangle into thirds, forming a 3-in. square. Place in <amount original_amount="a large" fraction="1.000000000000" units="large">a large</amount> greased bowl, turning once to grease the top. Cover and let rise at room temperature until almost doubled, about 1 hour.<img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-2\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-2" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-2", 3600)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Punch down dough and repeat folding process. Return dough to bowl; refrigerate, covered, overnight. </li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Grease the bottom of a disposable foil roasting pan with at least 4-in.-high sides; dust pan with cornmeal. Turn dough onto a floured surface. Knead gently 6-8 times; shape into a 6-in. round loaf. Place into prepared pan; dust top with remaining <amount original_amount="1 tablespoon" fraction="1.000000000000" units="tablespoon">1 tablespoon</amount> flour or sesame seeds (not both). Cover pan and let rise at room temperature until dough expands to a 7-½-in. loaf, about 1-¼ hours.<img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-3\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-3" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-3", 3600)</script><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-3", 900)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Preheat oven to 500°. Using a sharp knife, make a slash (¼ in. deep) across top of loaf. Cover pan tightly with foil. Bake on lowest oven rack 25 minutes. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-4\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-4" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-4", 1500)</script></div></li><li onclick="handleItemClick(this)"> Reduce oven setting to 450°. Remove foil; bake bread until deep golden brown, 25-30 minutes. Remove loaf to a wire rack to cool. <img src="images/alarm-clock-icon.png" onclick="toggleElement(\'CircularTimer-5\')" class="alarm-clock-icon"><div id="CircularTimer-5" class="circular-timer-container"><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-5", 1500)</script><script>new CircularTimer("CircularTimer-5", 1800)</script></div></li></ol>' ] );
